      <title>A Common Enemy</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10620#M10620</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Although there is plenty of threads scattered throughout the various cleric and druid forums about healing power, group desirability, dps, and basically anything short of what type of cracker goes best with cheez whiz, I think that maybe both classes are missing out what is truly most of the problem... the bot healer.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So what is to be done about it?&amp;nbsp; Is this something that will fade with time as the devs keep adding content that will make bot healers tough, if not impossible, to use as the sole healer in a group?&amp;nbsp; Or is there something that could be changed within the CLR/DRU spellsets and abilities now that would help?&amp;nbsp; The only thing I could come up with is making CHeal&amp;nbsp;non-usable except in raid settings, but I get the feeling that this isn't something that the devs are willing to alter atm... and I am also reluctant to suggest this since I am not starting this thread as flamebait.&amp;nbsp; I just believe if bots could be minimized outside the group that both clerics and druids (maybe shammies too *shrug*) would find themselves with more groups and less to argue over:smileyhappy:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;BTW, my main is a 70 druid.... the reason I posted this in the cleric discussion area is that clerics IMHO would have a better grasp on the various forms of healing that a druid doesn't have access to and thus could provide a better analysis and/or ideas on this topic.&amp;nbsp; Or, you guys could also tell me that I don't know **HALFLING** I am talking about and get the heck out of your forums LOL.&amp;nbsp; Also, any of the druid mains that post over here: Please try and restrict this thread to ideas and/or constructive criticism... there are FAR too many threads in this forum and in the druid forums that have devolved into "you're stoopid! no you're stoopid!" Maybe both classes can&amp;nbsp; have at least one thread we can just be civil with each other and talk rationally :smileyhappy:&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
