      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I agree that it's not just healers but any group slot that's available and/or needed.&amp;nbsp; The biggest issue is not in bots themselves (without bots some groups would simply either never form or break up for lack of a missing role filler), but in the fact that once a bot is in a group, no one in that group even considers replacing the bot with a real player later on.&amp;nbsp; I'm just as guilty of it as the next person, I have a druid bot which I use for porting, fixed invis, and DPS.&amp;nbsp; I typically try to get LFG guilmates who can fill the DPS role into my group and I will drop my druid, but chances if I am in RSS and a DPS classes shouts LFG I am vey unlikely to take that pickup person in.&amp;nbsp; It's the "better the devil you know" syndrome - an adequately botted toon is better than an unknown real person.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
